- Clinical exam: voluminous solid swelling on right hemiscrotum, penis retraction.  
- Blood marker: extremely high AFP (>53,000 µg/L).  
- Imaging: Ultrasound shows a large heterogeneous mass with solid and cystic/necrotic areas and vascularisation in the right hemiscrotum; absence of normal testicular and epididymal tissue on the right.  
- CT: confirms the right scrotal mass; no metastasis or lymphadenopathy noted.  
- Left testis and epididymis normal.  

