- CT shows a hyperdense mass in the right adnexa/paracervical region with intense heterogeneous arterial enhancement and areas of necrosis.
- MRI shows a heterogeneously iso to hyperintense lesion on T1, heterogeneously hyperintense on T2 (""light bulb sign""), restricted diffusion areas, preserved fat planes.
