1) White cord syndrome - matches acute postoperative neurological deficit, T2 hyperintensity in cord, mixed edema patterns, no haematoma or residual compression solely accounting for deficit.  
2) Compressive myelopathy - possible but less likely given acute onset and diffusion findings.  
3) Central cord syndrome - less likely due to clinical pattern and no specific traumatic injury pattern.  
