3) Localised ascites (least likely given the well-defined, encapsulated nature and catheter tip presence inside the cyst).  

The presence of a cystic subcapsular liver lesion scalloping the parenchyma and containing the VP shunt tip strongly favors the hepatic subcapsular CSF pseudocyst diagnosis.  
