18924,"Clinical History: 68-year-old male, a known case of chronic kidney disease (CKD) stage V on dialysis, complaints of swelling in the left forearm and difficulty in cannulation. The patient had a history of left brachiocephalic arteriovenous fistula formation with a polytetrafluoroethylene (PTFE) brachiocephalic graft. Local examination showed dilated tortuous swellings on the left forearm reaching up to the cubital fossa.
