18934,"Clinical History: A 65-year-old male presented with 2 days of severe right-sided lower abdominal pain. He was pyrexial with a raised neutrophil count (9.2x10^9/L) and CRP (55mg/L). Examination revealed right inguinal swelling and tenderness. Due to the high suspicion of incarcerated inguinal hernia, a CT abdomen and pelvis was requested.
