- MRI: T1/T2 heterogeneously hyperintense soft tissue lesion from right sacrum with exophytic pelvic component; multiple cystic areas consistent with blood degradation products; diffusion restriction; extension into S1-S2 foramina with nerve root encasement; heterogeneous post-contrast enhancement.  
- Clinical: Young patient, expansile lesion with cystic areas, blood degradation products on MRI, aggressive behavior with soft tissue infiltration and neural foramina involvement.

