- Pros: Age compatible; aggressive lesion with blood-filled cysts (multiloculated blood-filled spaces) typical; heterogeneous signal with hemorrhage; diffusion restriction common; soft tissue extension and cortical destruction consistent with malignant osteosarcoma; involvement of neural foramina and SI joint extension; aggressive local behavior.  
- Cons: Usually associated with aggressive periosteal reaction or matrix calcifications (not mentioned); bone matrix mineralization may be expected but not explicitly described.  
