   Pros: oligodendrogliomas classically show calcifications (up to 80% cases), often bilateral and frontal, may cause bone remodeling. Show increased choline and decreased NAA on spectroscopy. Usually minimal or no enhancement. No diffusion restriction. Typically have cortical and subcortical involvement. Good match.
