5) Hypoxic-ischemic encephalopathy  
Pros: Diffuse cortical and deep gray matter involvement possible; diffusion restriction common.  
Cons: Usually history of hypoxic episode or cardiac arrest; not described. Corpus callosum involvement can occur but is less symmetrical and usually patchy.

C) Ranking:  
