2) Osmotic demyelination syndrome – Some overlap but less specific due to absence of electrolyte disturbance and pontine involvement.  
3) Wernicke’s encephalopathy – Alcohol history present but MRI findings not classic.  
4) Hypoxic-ischemic encephalopathy – Less likely given history.  
