   - Pros: Chronic inflammatory lesion, can mimic carcinoma; often presents as painless mass.  
   - Cons: Typically not associated with systemic TB or immunosuppression; no features of inflammation on imaging described; lesion is lobulated and irregular but plasma cell mastitis often shows abscess or cystic changes.  
