1) Mammary tuberculosis - Pathognomonic: Pleural empyema with peripheral calcification and fluid suggests TB infection; immunosuppression predisposes to TB; breast lesion with inflammatory characteristics, no vascularity, and muscle invasion fits TB mastitis.  
