3) Idiopathic granulomatous mastitis - Possible in chronic inflammatory breast lesions, but less likely given systemic TB signs.  
4) Plasma cell mastitis - Less fit due to lack of typical plasma cell mastitis imaging appearance.  
5) Actinomycosis - Least likely due to rarity and lack of characteristic imaging findings.  

</analysis>  
