- Radiographs show superficial sclerosis of the patella with subtle erosion at the inferior pole, no fracture or soft tissue injury.  
- MRI shows patellar inferior pole hypointense on T1, hyperintense on PD fat-sat, diffusion restriction on DWI, mild effusion, and synovial thickening with enhancement.  
- Subchondral bone and articular cartilage largely intact.  

B) Candidate pass/fail with pros/cons:  
1) Post-traumatic bone contusion/fracture:  
   - Pros: Subtle erosion and edema may mimic contusion.  
   - Cons: No trauma history, no fracture seen radiographically, MRI suggests infection rather than contusion (diffusion restriction, synovial enhancement).  
2) Post-traumatic bone osteochondral defect:  
   - Pros: MRI edema and erosion could indicate osteochondral defect.  
