19086,"Clinical History: A 22-year-old female presented with dysphagia for 9 years and gradually increasing vulval swelling for 5 years. Clinical examination revealed a firm, non-tender, lobulated mass (~8x8 cm) involving bilateral labia with intact overlying skin. Upper gastrointestinal endoscopy showed a bulge in the mid and lower oesophagus with intact mucosa and luminal narrowing.
