A) Key findings:  
- Young female (22 years) with long-standing dysphagia and gradual vulval swelling.  
- MRI thorax: long segment thickening of lower thoracic oesophagus extending to gastric cardia, T1 isointense, T2 mildly hyperintense, mild homogeneous enhancement, smooth outline, clear planes with adjacent structures.  
- MRI pelvis: large lobulated mass involving clitoral region and bilateral labia majora, T1 isointense, T2 hyperintense, diffusion restriction, marked homogeneous enhancement, no cystic/necrotic areas or fat/calcifications.  
