- Cons: Sarcomas often show necrosis, heterogeneous enhancement, more irregular margins; no calcifications or cystic changes; PET SUV high but sarcomas less commonly present as diffuse circumferential smooth esophageal thickening. Also, sarcoma involving both oesophagus and vulva simultaneously is rare.  

