   Cons: Usually aggressive soft tissue mass; diffusion restriction and large lesion expected; no solid mass or diffusion restriction here

6) Scurvy
   Pros: Can cause periosteal reaction and soft tissue swelling
   Cons: Usually subperiosteal hemorrhages, ring apophysis; less likely in 6 months old; no nutritional history

