   Pros: Rare, similar to Caffey disease; infantile onset
   Cons: Rare alternative to Caffey; no distinct imaging differences given

9) Prolonged PGE1 infusion
   Pros: Causes periosteal reaction and edema
   Cons: No history of PGE1 therapy; unlikely in this context

