3) Liposarcoma (malignancy less likely due to encapsulation and no restricted diffusion).  
4) Hibernoma (fat content fits but lacks prominent vessels and septations).  
5) Lipoma (unlikely due to complex features and vessels).  
6) Fat necrosis (least likely due to well-defined, encapsulated nature).  
Thus, the best fit is angiomyolipoma.  
