A) Key findings:  
- Demographics: 23-year-old woman (young adult).  
- Clinical presentation: 2 weeks of abdominal distension, pelvic pain, urinary frequency.  
- Imaging: Large left retro-uterine ovarian mass (17x16x12 cm), predominantly solid, heterogeneous enhancement, no macroscopic fat or calcifications.  
- Post-gadolinium MRI: intermediate T2 signal, avid enhancement, scattered cystic-necrotic areas.  
- DWI: marked hyperintensity with low ADC values (high cellularity).  
- Displacement of uterus and ureters, moderate bilateral hydroureteronephrosis.  
- Tumor-uterus interface smooth; right ovary normal but displaced anteriorly.  
