19118,"Clinical History: An 11-year-old premenarche girl presented with a 3-week history of intermittent hypogastric pain, not being able to sleep for more than two hours at a time for the last 5 days. Clinical examination revealed a palpable pelvic mass and suprapubic tenderness. The patient had no other relevant findings on physical examination. Blood and urine tests were all within normal limits.
