- CT: left renal enlargement, destruction of parenchymal architecture, dilated calyces showing ""bear paw sign,"" blurring of perirenal fat, psoas muscle enlargement and abscess, nephroureterolithiasis, nonfunctional left kidney on excretory phase.  
