19157,"Clinical History: A 5-year-old girl presented with a progressively enlarging occipital swelling and mild pain. She had prior right-eye surgeries for eyelid coloboma, with corneal opacification of uncertain cause. She had no light perception in the right eye and reduced vision in the left. No systemic issues. Siblings were healthy.
