1) Oculocerebrocutaneous syndrome (Delleman syndrome)  
   - Pros: Bilateral ocular colobomas, CNS lipomas, scalp/skull anomalies (bony defects), midline brain anomalies possible.  
   - Cons: Usually midline or paramedian skin defects, focal alopecia, orbital cysts; the description doesn't mention typical skin lesions; arachnoid cyst less typical. However, the presence of bilateral colobomas plus intracranial lipomas and skull defects fits well.  

