B) Candidate pass/fail with pros/cons:  
1. Dysplastic cerebellar gangliocytoma (Lhermitte-Duclos disease):  
   - Pros: Occurs in cerebellar hemisphere and vermis; shows thickened cerebellar folia with alternating T2 hyper- and hypointensity showing ""tigroid"" or ""tiger-striped"" pattern on imaging; associated with bony remodeling due to slow growth.  
