19160,"Clinical History: A 28-year-old pregnant female presented to the neurology department with new-onset generalised tonic-clonic seizures. Neurological examination was normal. A dermatological consultation revealed multiple acneiform scars over the flexor surface and pearly papules along the eyelid margins and on the forehead (Figures 1 and 2), for which she had been under evaluation. No family history of similar illness was noted. MRI brain was performed to investigate the aetiology of seizures.
