19161,"Clinical History: A 42-year-old woman taking etanercept for psoriatic arthritis presented to the emergency department with pain in her right wrist for three weeks, predominantly in the fourth and fifth fingers. She reported no history of trauma or prior procedures. Clinical examination revealed swelling on the palmar surface and pain with movement. An ultrasound was performed, which showed synovial fluid (images not available).
